spans.text: 报幕
It seems like I've caught some inspiration again... but it's not enough...
So, what should I do today——
(Besides the heart, there are no abnormalities in the body... The expected fatigue and lack of oxygen are not present.)
(……Perhaps when the countdown ends, I will live as a person without a heartbeat?)
(Then I don't want to go to the hospital in my life, how can I participate in band activities if I get caught and studied?)
(But... if I meet other people, I still have to pay attention to physical contact.)
The heartbeat that rings every six seconds has become almost imperceptible, and she is now no different from a doll.
The last complete day…
There should be no other choice for that one remaining thing.
Just as Taki was thinking about her schedule for the day, the desktop suddenly emitted a muffled warning.
"If you're free, let's meet up tonight? You can come directly to me after work. Everyone has been worried about you since last time.
I might have to go to Hokkaido in a few days.
"No need to reply."
At this juncture... to keep an appointment. Taki Shiina rubbed her face, her cheeks were stiff, whether it was because she had just woken up or for some other reason.
She admitted that her acting skills were quite poor, and she had no ability to confirm a hysteria-like crisis without arousing suspicion. Does she think she is Anon Chihaya or Soyo Nagasaki?
The scalding concern and soft inquiries were what Taki Shiina found difficult to resist. The best way not to be exposed is to shrink into her own territory.
Although Taki Shiina herself cannot guarantee 100% what is wrapped inside, the person with the answer has only one guess.
(I'll always know, what the result will be. In a few days.)
Taki Shiina put her phone back on the desk, back where she originally placed it.
(She said there's no need to reply... but there's no one who decides to go to an appointment without saying a word.)
"Okay."
Once people encounter setbacks in the present, they tend to have a nostalgic psychology.
Since everyone moved out of their original residences, the distance to RiNG, which they used to frequent in high school, has become a problem.

Over the years, they have gradually accumulated more fans, and the venues for performances have gradually expanded. When she came back to her senses, the place that carried Taki's earliest memories of MyGO!!!!! had been placed in a small corner of her memory.
(It's too far to go back... I'll ride my motorcycle.)
Taki pushed out the motorcycle that she hadn't used for a long time from the garage, checked that there was enough fuel in the tank, and skillfully straddled it, heading towards the city.
What is it...
Taki always feels like there's something important she hasn't done yet...
Something that... if she doesn't do it now, she will definitely regret it for the rest of her life, no, she will regret it even in death...
Thank goodness, thank goodness, thank goodness, the tickets that I pre-ordered three months in advance were delivered last week, I almost forgot about it.
(Limited edition panda baby exhibition... I remember the tickets were placed in...)
(Who is it at this time...)
She looked out the window, where the countdown on the window glass was looming in the morning light, the deadline seemed more concrete than ever.
(No wasting time... How did I meet deadlines before?)

The empty energy jelly wrappers in the trash can silently answered her question——when she was too busy, eating was indeed the first thing to be given up, and the gelatinous food glued the afternoon and evening into a whole period of uninterrupted inspiration, a complete time.
(But I can't eat this every day, right.)
(If I really eat this every day, it seems like the reserves at home won't be enough...)
In any case, let's go to the supermarket, buy everything at once, and buy some other dishes.

The list she came up with was a bit longer than she expected, and it seemed that her motorcycle couldn't carry a week's worth of groceries at once. She checked one last time to see if there was anything she had forgotten to add, and went downstairs to call a car to the supermarket.
The empty energy jelly wrapper lay alone on top of the trash can——that was the last one.

Under the busy schedule of the past few days, she rarely even ate convenience store box lunches, let alone the ever-increasing amount of time spent composing music late into the night, which further accelerated the consumption of these meal replacements. And the stock in the refrigerator had long since run out.
How long has it been since I had a good breakfast...
Let's go to the supermarket, and buy some ingredients I want to cook, and cook one last meal myself.
The list I came up with was a bit longer than I expected, although there are only [@v100] days left, it's always better to buy more than less.

It seems that my motorcycle can't carry such a load of dishes at once. She checked one last time to see if there was anything she had forgotten to add, and went downstairs to call a car to the supermarket.

Since I'm going out tonight anyway, I might as well not stay at home today. I also have to hand over the follow-up courses at the music classroom to the institution, it's not a good idea to keep asking for leave.
Didn't I tell little Hina last time that I was going to check her homework in this class?
Urging children to practice hard, but taking leave in a grand manner myself, what's that all about.
Let's pack up and go to class, and then go find Soyo after work.
During the days spent with her teammates, Taki encountered a lot of inspiration.
Those precious notes that could never appear around a lonely person still need to be sorted out to be transformed into melodies.
(…There's no time to waste.)
(I must complete it.)
(Is this okay... I just hung up on my sister's phone...)
Before she knew it, her finger had already pressed the call button, and Taki's breathing stopped for a moment.
Taki? What's wrong?
Ah, sister... I mean, I have time today.
...Why didn't you say so just now?
Uh, sister, you just arrived in Japan, right? If it's inconvenient, then forget it...
Sigh...
I'll come when I'm done with what I'm doing, remember to send me the address.
After hanging up the phone, Taki sighed and began to prepare for her sister's visit.
(By the way, I wonder if my sister is free today. If I don't contact her, maybe there won't be another chance to meet...)
Having made up her mind, Taki dialed Maki's number.
Hello? Taki?
Sister, are you free today?
Yeah, I happen to be free, I'll come find you.
(My sister's action is still so strong...)
After hanging up the phone, Taki sighed and began to prepare for her sister's visit.
(The progress of the song is only halfway through.)
(There is only... 1 day left.)
(But, I can't rush...)
(Because I can do it.)
After writing this, I need to stop and rest for 20 minutes and clean the room.
According to the current state, I can finish the sub-melody in the evening.
If there are no reworks, I can complete the B section overnight.
No, staying up all night and overdrawing my body will only lower the efficiency during the day.
Set an alarm clock and start working.
No, this part can't be arranged too full, I have to consider Raana's impromptu style at any time.
The pitch range can't be too high, Tomori's vocal range isn't there.
The rhythm guitar and bass changes should be richer.
Drums......
If it were me, this bpm would be fine now.
...Let's do it again.
(This is... the last day.)
No... no, there must be something more important than this...
Okay, let's finish the song in one go.
In the morning, before the busy crowds have woken up and the vehicles have not yet started making noise
Before pressing the piano keys, I can hear the sound of swallows that I haven't heard for many years.
Spring is here.
